14/04/2005
STRASBOURG, France -- Addressing the European Parliament in Strasbourg Wednesday (13 April), EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn praised the tangible progress Western Balkan countries have made in terms of EU integration. He stressed that this year and next year would be crucial for the region, highlighting two issues as most important on the agenda -- successful completion of the work of the UN war crimes tribunal and resolution of Kosovo's status. Rehn added that in November, the European Commission would present the enlargement package and detailed reports on each individual country. (EU Web site - 13/04/05)
